qas.question: Along with the Hargesian culture, what culture was present in Somalia in the Stone age?
What undeciphered writings were found alongside the rock paintings?
During what period did the Doian culture thrive?

context: <a1_0>Inscriptions<a1_0/> have been found beneath many of the rock paintings, but archaeologists have so far been unable to decipher this form of ancient writing. During <a2_0>the Stone age<a2_0/>, <a0_0>the Doian culture<a0_0/> and the Hargeisan culture flourished here with their respective industries and factories.
